description:
Rodolphe was a school teacher who's eye desease had prevented him from becoming a professional artist like his father before him. He drew his first comic, a word that didn't exist back then, in the late 1820s. He didn't publish it then but rewrote/redrew it and published his first work The Adventures of Mr. Obadiah Oldbuck #1 in French in 1837.

Because there were no copyright laws his work was translated and pirated to many countries in the world.
name: Rodolphe Töpffer

description:
Ahokoivu was born in Oulu, Finland.

She has studied making comics in the art school of Liminka and Angouleme.

She usually works as a teacher of making comics, but also publishes them from time to time.
name: Mari Ahokoivu
